```
In `Services/FileService.cs`, the `Browse` method calls `Directory.GetDirectories(full)` and then `Directory.GetFiles(full)`, walking the directory twice and materializing two arrays. Replace with a SINGLE enumeration. The cleanest approach is `new DirectoryInfo(full).EnumerateFileSystemInfos()` which yields both files and directories in one pass; for each `FileSystemInfo`, branch on `(info is DirectoryInfo)` / `(info is FileInfo)` (or on `info.Attributes.HasFlag(FileAttributes.Directory)`) to build the same `FileEntryDto` values. You may alternatively use `Directory.EnumerateFileSystemEntries(full)` and stat each entry, but the `DirectoryInfo.EnumerateFileSystemInfos` approach avoids the extra stat. Preserve the EXACT output contract: directories first then files, each group sorted by name (OrdinalIgnoreCase) via the existing `CompareEntries` helper; each entry's Name (info.Name), Path (ToRelative of the full path), IsDirectory, Size (0 for directories, info.Length for files), LastModified (info.LastWriteTimeUtc). The FolderCount/FileCount/TotalSize aggregations and the `parent = ComputeParent(relative)` computation must be unchanged. Do not change any other method. The lazy `Root` accessor added by task-16 (if landed) must be used in place of the previous `_root` field. Verification: `dotnet test TestProject.Tests/TestProject.Tests.csproj` — all `Browse_*` tests in FileServiceTests still pass.

